cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

The paper deals with information geometry, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the axiomatic characterization of conditional information geometry. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the primal problems underlying logistic regression and AdaBoost. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the geometry of conditional models. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the geometry of conditional distributions. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with information and its geometric properties.
